#GOOGL This setup is usually called a 'Breakout Failure Trade' 
Identify a Congestion zone. Two to Three consecutive bars with closing within previous candle's range (High - Low) 
Look for a Breakout bar. (Candle stick with the close above below the congestion zone. 
For a Bearish breakout (which was the case here shown in $GOOGL )- look for a Bullish bar next day - which becomes your Setup Bar, and place a buy stop order above the high of Setup bar. 
If price triggers an entry - U are IN !! 
Opposite for a Bullish breakout Failure setup.

$AMZN 3500c trade manage 

I got in 3500c at the break of 3455. However the breakout got rejected in the morning. Meaning the initial breakout attempt failed.

These things are bound to happen as part of your trading. Overall higher time period chart is still Bullish for AMZN, so I actively managed my position by buying at Key Price levels only. U don't buy just because you are down in something, you only add at KEY price levels - so there is a good chance that price will bounce from those levels temporarily at least. 

Not applicable every time. Of course you have to evaluate in bigger time frame to see if it is worth averaging down or taking a Stop-loss
